KCB Group has said it will inject Sh50 billion in innovations the next five years as it looks to boost earnings from digital banking platforms. In partnership with global technological giant Oracle, the lender yesterday hosted more than 200 technology developers from across Africa. The developers who will engage in a week long Hackathon Challenge, are expected to come up with cutting edge solutions. The future of banking is digital and we are deliberately aligning ourselves to this, KCB chief executive and managing director Joshua Oigara said.The programme is expected to create 2.5 million jobs for the youth through an app that will connect entrepreneurs.